    <p>{`One last disclaimer: In its current implementation, the ToC does not update when adding new headings to a page after the page has loaded. In most cases, pages are static once the user has loaded them so theres no point in wasting CPU cycles on a DOM observer. But just in case your ToC should update to include new headings even while the user is viewing a page, you might want to take a look at the `}<a parentName="p" {...{
        "href": "https://developer.mozilla.org/docs/Web/API/MutationObserver"
